                  <handDesc>
                    <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                      <desc>Columetric layout of text:
                        <locus target="#121v" facs="123">fols. 121v, </locus> (Ps. 148),
                        <locus target="#121v #122r #122v #123r" facs="123 124">121v, 122r, 122v, 123r, </locus> (Ps. 150),
                        <locus target="#132r #132v" facs="133 134">132r, 132v</locus> (tenth biblical canticle)</desc>
                    </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#ir(ecto)" facs="001">Fol. ir(ecto)</locus> two crosses, crudely painted.</decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d2">
                      Decorative designs:
                      <locus target="#8r #13v #23v #42r #48v #59r #70r #78r #84r #97r #109r #111v #117r #123r #135v #136r #142r #143r #144v #146r #147r #148r #149r" facs="009 015 025 043 050 060 071 079 085 098 110 113 118 124 137 137 143 144 146 147 148 149 150">folss. 8r, 13v, 23v, 42r, 48v, 59r, 70r, 78r, 84r, 97r, 109r, 111v, 117r, 123r, 135v, 136r, 142r, 143r, 144v, 146r, 147r, 148r, 149r, </locus> (dotted line using alternating black and red);
                      <locus target="#149v" facs="151">149v, </locus> (dotted line using red);
                      <locus target="#152r" facs="153">152r</locus> (division using combined dots and lines in red).
                    </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3">
                      <desc><locus target="#iv(erso)" facs="002">Fol. iv(erso)</locus><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1012Equestrian">Equestrian Saint</ref>, Joab and his brother Abishai (1Sam 26:6), each on horseback </desc>
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                    <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                          <locus target="#152v #153r #153v" facs="154 155">Fols. 152v, 153r, 153v</locus>
                           <desc>Symbolic interpretation of parts of a church building and its contents, in Amharic. (see Marcel Griaule, “Regles de l’Église Éthiopiens (Documents Éthiopiens),” JA, vol. 221 (1932), pp. 1–42),
                             with incipit <foreign xml:lang="am">ሥርዓተ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ታቦቱ፡ ክርስቶስ። መንበሩ፡ ፬እንስሳ። ሥዕሉ፡ በክርሠ፡ ማርያም፡ እንደ፡ ኃደረ።<gap reason="omitted"/></foreign>
                           </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                          <locus target="#152v" facs="154">Fol. 152v</locus>
                           <desc>Excerpt from , <title type="incomplete" corresp="LIT3851Hassab"/>.
                          (For a detailed study of the computus, see Otto Neugebaur, Ethiopic Astronomy, Vienna 1970),
                          and  <foreign xml:lang="am">ጌታቸው፡ ኃይሌ፥ ባሕረ፡ ሐሳብ፡ የዘመን፡ ቈጠራ፡ ቅርሳችን፡ ከታሪክ፡ ማስታወሻ፡ ጋር፡</foreign> Collegeville (Minnesota), 1993 EC)
                        </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                          <locus target="#153r" facs="154">Fol. 153r</locus>
                           <desc>First part of the <title type="incomplete" cert="medium" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT6205Saalnaka">Saʾalnāka maḥari
                                                  saʾalnāka faṭāri saʾalnāka kahali</title></desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                          <locus target="#153r" facs="154">Fol. 153r</locus>
                           <desc>Prayer to de-consecrate blessed baptismal water (Unfinished), cf. EMIP 32, f. 38r,
                             with incipit
                             <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዝንቱ፡ ጸሎተ፡ ፍትሐተ፡ ማይ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ አምላክነ፡ አኃዜ፡ ኵሉ፡ ፍጥረት፡ እምኀበ፡ አልቦ፡ በጥበብከ፡ በአማን፡ አስተጋብእኮሙ፡ ለማያት፡<gap reason="omitted"/></foreign></desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                          <locus target="#153v" facs="155">Fol. 153v</locus>
                           <desc type="CalendaricNote">Calendar of the Apostles, Evangelists and few other holy days</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc>The codex has been rebound in disorder</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc><locus target="#1r" facs="002">Fol. 1r</locus> (top margin) insufficiently legible text of one line</desc></item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                          <locus target="#20v #122v #143r" facs="022 124 144">Fols. 20v, 122v, 143r</locus>).
                           <desc>Overlooked lines are written interlinearly</desc>
                           </item>
                        <item xml:id="e4">
                          <locus target="#132v" facs="134">Fol. 132v</locus>
                          <desc>An overlooked line was written in the upper margin and a mark was made in the text
                          where it was to be inserted, but another scribe has written the overlooked line
                          (beginning with the + symbol) into the text interlinearly a line lower than the location marked in the first case</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e5">
                          <locus target="#39v #44r #45r #124r" facs="041 045 046 125">Fols. 39v, 44r, 45r, 124r</locus>
                           <desc>etc., some long lines of text have been written in smaller letters to avoid forcing the line of text onto another line</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e6">
                          <locus target="#65r" facs="066">Fol. 65r</locus>
                           <desc>A small, black and red cross marks the midpoint of the Psalms</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a6">
                          <locus target="#70r" facs="071">Fol. 70r</locus>;
                           <desc>Prayer for the soul of <foreign xml:lang="gez">ገብረ፡ ኢየሱስ፡</foreign></desc>
                           </item>
                        <item xml:id="a7">
                          <locus target="#84r #109r" facs="085 110"> f. 84r, 109r, and passim</locus>
                          <desc>Prayer for the soul of <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወልደ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡</foreign></desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a8">
                          <locus target="#148v" facs="150">Fol. 148v</locus>
                          <desc>Prayer for the soul of <foreign xml:lang="gez">ተክለ፡ ሃይማኖት፡</foreign></desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e7">
                          <locus target="#8 #23 #52 #59 #61 #67 #70 #78 #84 #94 #97 #109 #117" facs="009 024 053 060 062 068 071 079 085 095 098 110 118">Fols. 8, 23, 52, 59, 61, 67, 70, 78, 84, 94, 97, 109, 117</locus>
                          <desc>Various colored string sewn into corners of to mark content divisions</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e8">
                          <desc>This codex has been rebound.
                            There are several clues to the architecture of the original codex and of the rebound version:
                            reinforcement strips surround several quires, original quire numbers are visible on several folios, and the strings are visible at the center of several quires.
                            Nevertheless, it will require a very detailed study to sort out the two systems with any certainty</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e9">
                          <locus target="#39v #44r #45r #124r" facs="041 045 046 125">Fols. 39v, 44r, 45r, 124r</locus>
                          <desc>etc., some long lines of text have been written in smaller letters to avoid forcing the line of text onto another line</desc>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                    <binding xml:id="binding" contemporary="partly">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Four repaired Coptic chain stitches attached with bridle attachments to rough–hewn boards.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                           <material key="wood"/>
                        </decoNote>
                    </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
               </physDesc>
